column1: DP92 - Delete Product - Set Status
column33: Verify that the system allows changing the product's status from "In stock" to "Out of stock" and vice versa.
column76:
The steps have been completed successfully.
The system displays the message "Product status updated successfully".
The product's status has been changed from "In stock" to "Out of stock" as expected.
column88:
Display the message "Product status updated successfully".
The product's status is updated accurately in the database.
The product's new status appears in the product list (e.g. "In stock" or "Out of stock").
column106:
1. Log in to the system.
2. Navigate to the product listing page.
3. Select the product whose status needs to be changed (for example, "Product J").
4. Click the "Edit" button next to the product.
5. Change product status:
If the current status is "In stock", change it to "Out of stock".
If the current status is "Out of stock", change it to "In stock".
6. Press the "Save" button to save the changes.
